nd paced to fit its place in the race efficient  flexible we believe that timeliness and reliability are key attributes for any capital partner with the benefit of institutional knowledge gained over almost a decade together the marathons team can react quickly and thoughtfully to new opportunities we bring a fresh perspective and take a flexible approach to developing taxefficeient capital solutions company leadership vincent chok managing director  cofounder mr chok has gained broad business experience in the canadian exempt securities market raising capital with a number of canadian real estate based offerings for commercial real estate acquisitions land developments and mortgage financing through private investment syndications douglas r e wilson managing director  cofounder a senior executive with over thirty years of business experience mr wilson has wideraning experience in industries including marketing services telecommunications corporate finance and governance consulting and consumer credit services dan horner director  legal counsel  cofounder mr horner is currently a partner in the law firm of scott venturo llp in calgary canada he carries on a corporate and commercial law practice including significant acquisitions real estate development commercial lending and financing marathon asset management  new york based fund     career opportunities      contact us    investor login   bestinclass investment manager focused on opportunistic investing in credit and fixed income markets globally utilizing marathons integrated platform deep fundamental research and situational expertise about marathon strategies opportunistic credit investing firm overview investment philosophy business principles philanthropy capabilities leadership public private investment partnership corporate credit structured credit emerging markets credit separate account platform private funds platform marathon asset management announces strategic investment by blackstone it’s a ‘g’ thing 