ten intricate risk guidelines investment horizons and return requirements reliable partner the marathon team has built robust longlasting relationships with middle market companies management teams financial sponsors lending institutions and deal intermediaries we bring a collaborative approach to our investment process and focus on providing flexible structuring alternatives straightforward discussions efficient diligence processes and reliable execution a simple philosophy at marathon we believe that economic success for companies as well as individuals and families is reliant on steady and considered strategies applied over the long run each phase of activity whether short term trading for profits or a multigenerational approach husbanding assets in the course of the affairs of a company a family or an individual must be tailored and paced to fit its place in the race efficient  flexible we believe that timeliness and reliability are key attributes for any capital partner with the benefit of institutional knowledge gained over almost a decade together the marathons team can react quickly and thoughtfully to new opportunities we bring a fresh perspective and take a flexible approach to developing taxefficeient capital solutions company leadership vincent chok managing director  cofounder mr chok has gained broad business experience in the canadian exempt securities market raising capital with a number of canadian real estate based offerings for commercial real estate acquisitions land developments and mortgage financing through private investment syndications douglas r e wilson managing director  cofounder a senior executive with over thirty years of business experience mr wilson has wideraning experience in industries including marketing services telecommunications corporate finance and governance consulting and consumer credit services dan horner director  legal counsel  cofounder mr horner is currently a partner in the law firm of scott venturo llp in calgary canada he carries on a corporate and commercial law practice including significant acquisitions real estate development commercial lending and financing   forbidden access is denied server error   forbidden access is denied you do not have permission to view this directory or page using the credentials that you supplied investment banking firm  financial advisory firm  renewable energy  marathon capital marathon capital investment bankers  for global energy and infrastructure markets in this white paper marathon capital explores how a decrease in corporate income tax rates and other proposed corporate tax changes could impact the us renewable energy financing landscape the white paper represents marathon capitals commitment to helping renewable energy developers investors and other market participants better understand the renewable energy opportunity us federal corporate tax rate reform – potential impact on us renewable power financing is available here marathon capital’s ceo ted brandt was recently named 7 in the top  power people in wind for  by the uk based publication a word about wind visit a word about wind here we look forward to seeing you at marathon capitals relocated headquarters visit our contact us page to update company information and our people page to update individual contact information  marathon capital has been awarded “best renewable asset ma advisor” in power finance  risk’s annual power finance deals and firms awards      the firm overview people business industry focus services approach transactions resources recent news careers contact us subscribe return home print this page sitemap privacy policy terms of use  7 marathon capital llc all rights reserved  member finra sipc  marathon capital management  rancho cucamonga ca microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow firstparty and thirdparty cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to not delete browsing 